Singleton Class

Jre is having a class ResourceBundle as a singleton class

how to create a object : ResourceBundle rb = ResourceBundle.getBundle("baseName");
                         Calander c = Calander.getInstance();
                         
factory-method = 'methodname' to create object of a class using factory method.

Factory : returns other class objects
Singleton: returns own object

factory classes : logger factory, validater factory.. session fectory

use of factory classes:

	Hide instention
	by returning the instane of interface..make clients independs..
	
	e.g. :: Driver.getConnection(;;;) it returns the connection object it deos metter which is
	the data base--->>oracle,mysql.psql..etc
	
	Here connection is a interface
	
	
	In this example beans returns interface object....